        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Position Summary: </strong> The Shingo Institute, a program in the Jon M. Huntsman School of Business at Utah State University in Logan, has created the new position of Marketing Coordinator to help manage the marketing team’s day-to-day operations. The position will report to the Marketing and Communications Manager and be a member of the senior staff working with a graphic artist and two student employees who handle social media and video production. To get a good idea of what the Shingo Institute does, visit Shingo.org.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Responsibilities: </strong>
            <ul style="list-style: disc inside">
                <li>Workshop materials management, including working with various printers to get bids and print materials.</li>
                <li>Marketing calendar management. Help to create and maintain the marketing calendar and see that it is being followed.</li>
                <li>Newsletter content management.</li>
                <li>Press release management.</li>
                <li>Receipt handling and management.</li>
                <li>List management.</li>
                <li>Management of social media ads and remarketing ads (also known as retargeting).</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Required Qualifications:</strong>
            <ul style="list-style: disc inside">
                <li>Porificient with the Microsoft Office suite (Word, Excel, Powerpoint).</li>
